Package: simpleRevdepcheck
Type: Package
Title: Lightweight Reverse Dependency Checks
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Brantly", family = "Callaway", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "brantly.callaway@uga.edu")
    )
Description: Quickly run reverse dependency checks for a target package with a
    small dependency graph. Downloads reverse dependencies from CRAN, installs
    or upgrades their dependencies, runs checks in parallel, and summarizes
    results. Also supports checking GitHub development versions of packages
    alongside CRAN versions, using git clone. Designed to be lighter-weight
    than the 'revdepcheck' workflow when you expect most packages to pass with
    your new package version.
SystemRequirements: git (for github_deps support in simple_revdep_check())
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: rcmdcheck, utils, tools
Suggests: pak, devtools, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
